In this episode of So This Happened, we reviewed the indefinite suspension of Twitter by the Federal Government on Friday. The Minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed announced that the platform was suspended because of persistent use of the platform for activities capable of undermining Nigeria’s cooperate existence. After six years of leading the people of Abia State, Governor Okezie Ikpeazu proudly lists the presence of fast food outlets; Dominos Pizza and Chicken Republic as some of his achievements in the state. Lastly, speaking of toxic relationships, a man assaulted his wife for feeding his children with Garri (cassava flakes) in Lagos.